parameters: Melos the Hole Digger: I'm counting on you.
Melos the Hole Digger: Where could it be...

Melos the Hole Digger: It's the girl who came to the
Adventurer's Guild three years ago! Wow, you've grown so
strong.
Clea: I came here to fulfill my own purpose.

Melos the Hole Digger: I can understand it as an
adventurer, but it's a little complicated...

Melos the Hole Digger: Actually, I have a daughter, and as
a parent, I don't want her to seek revenge.
Clea: Because it's something I've decided.

Melos the Hole Digger: Haha, those who are stopped by words
aren't adventurers. After all, I'm called the 'Hole Digger'
for a reason.

Melos the Hole Digger: Researching ruins is my job. It's
something that naturally comes with a nickname based on my
work and personality.

Melos the Hole Digger: I'm looking forward to what kind of
nickname you'll have. By the way, do you have any business
with me?
Clea: The guild master asked me to collect some documents.

Melos the Hole Digger: It's about the report for the job.
Sorry, but could you hand it over to the guild master for
me?

Clea: Your complexion looks better than before... You've
really regained your energy... I'm glad...
Girl Ect: Please... don't leave me alone...
実績 三原則より大切なもの
隊列歩行の演出やそもそも階段前で出待ちの様子で
違和感を感じるため自動実行にしてます
Cleric Sophia: W-What happened? P-Please tell me!

Clea: The Adventurers Guild, Ftera, has decided to join
forces to make Prince Rex the king.
Thief Nora: Yay! That's great news, Sophia-san!

Mage Relm: So the opponent is the Imperial Palace... The
Adventurers Guild really loves [adventure], don't they...

Cleric Sophia: Thank you so much, Clea-chan... I'm really
happy that we can get Prince Rex's cooperation.

Cleric Sophia: I'm also happy that I can fight alongside
you.
Clea: Me too, let's fight together.

Clea (The birth of a new dragon... If it's really possible,
I'll definitely try to stop it)
Clea (For the me of that day)
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置
Young female explorer Ect: Thank you so much for today!
Young female explorer Ect: This is not much, but...
Clea: I'm looking forward to the future.

Young female explorer Ect: Ahaha, this is like a farewell
gift for my promotion!

Young female explorer Ect: If there's anything, I'll make a
request! Clea-san, please be sure to reach out if you ever
need help.
Clea: Yes, I'm counting on you.
Young female explorer Ect: Yeah! See you later!

Young female explorer Ect: Um, my dad's documents are
here... I'll submit the report that I put together...

Young female explorer Ect: It's pitch black outside! I
should head back to the dormitory and prepare for dinner...

Young female explorer Ect: There's no one in that room...
My dad is still missing.
Young female explorer Ect: Is that really true...?

Young female explorer Ect: There was a person named Psema
who came during the investigation... The Adventurer's Guild
has a [Black Request Form].

Young female explorer Ect: There are cases where they kill
people who are no longer useful... Could it be that my dad
was killed by the people from the guild--

Young female explorer Ect: The gem is shining... I wonder
what this feeling is.

Young female explorer Ect: I have to investigate... the
person who killed my dad...

Young female explorer Ect: They must definitely be inside
the Adventurer's Guild!
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置

parameters: ※※※該当イベント（シート単位）発生時の処理※※※
左記の出現条件をイベントと揃える
※※※該当イベント（シート単位）終了後は条件に1足して空に※※※
最後には左記の通り、スイッチを条件に空のページを設定
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置

Storge of Love: It's quite a large group, is something
happening?

Clea: I have something I want to confirm with the guild
master regarding the acceptance of Oplo's request...

Storge of Love: They should be coming soon. We made a
promise to have a meeting here.
Storge of Love: I'll at least ask for some details.

Storge of Love: The first guild master, Prus... at least,
they don't exist in the guild's archives.
Storge of Love: That's right, Celis?

Celis of the Swift Wind: The only ones in the Adventurer's
Guild are the [Seven Adventurers] who were created as a
fairy tale.

Celis of the Swift Wind: Other than that, there are only
fragmentary pieces of information about Proposi, the
negotiator who was the second guild master of Piste.

Celis of the Swift Wind: The first guild master, Prus, was
widely popular among the masses, just like the infamous Red-
Armed Zoe, so there is a mix of fiction and reality
surrounding them.

Celis of the Swift Wind: Because of that, there are fake
books and documents created, making the search as difficult
as the Fool's Grimoire.

Celis of the Swift Wind: Personally, there is a high
possibility that the Adventurer's Guild at that time
discarded information related to Piste and Proposi, in order
to create a sense of mystery.
Celis of the Swift Wind: I only know this much.
Clea: I-I've never talked for this long before...
Guild Master Agonia: It's noisy, but is there a problem?
Clea: More than a problem, it's more of a surprise...

Clea: Actually, there's something I want to discuss with
the guild master.

Guild Master Agonia: Searching for the roots of the
Adventurer's Guild is very meaningful to us as well.

Proposi with a Single Arm: So, does that mean you interpret
it as being willing to take on the task?

Guild Master Agonia: Of course, Clea, who has been
appointed, will be in charge.

Proposi with a Single Arm: I think I'll investigate the
area around Camps based on my own information.

Proposi with a Single Arm: If you find any new information,
please check the bulletin board at Camps.

Storge of Benevolence: It's good that we've accepted,
but... we don't have any information at all, do we?

Guild Master Agonia: If Clea and her connections have
access to a place where investigation was not possible
despite having reliable information, it might be worth
checking.

Guild Master Agonia: The Great Rock Castle is said to be
the hometown of negotiator Proposi. They might have their
own information.

Clea: Understood, I will consult with Mr. Reso at the Great
Rock Castle.
Guild Master Agonia: Will Celis also be accompanying?

Celis of the Swift Wind: I believe it is necessary for the
guild.
Guild Master Agonia: There is something I want you to do--

Celis of the Swift Wind: I believe it is necessary for the
guild.
Guild Master Agonia: Understood, please go.

Storge of Benevolence: Well, isn't that fine! It seems like
he has a fondness for Pluce after all.

Guild Master Agonia: Wait, please. You will be acting as a
substitute for Celis' request along with me.

Guild Master Agonia: Please make sure to perform
maintenance on our weapons, as we will be dealing with
around 50 bandits.
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置

Archaeologist Paryo: I'm sorry for going out of my way to
come here.
Clea: Your complexion doesn't look good. Are you okay?

Archaeologist Paryo: I am collecting various things related
to the history of the empire.

Archaeologist Paryo: Every item I collect has a story
behind it, whether it's something I excavated, purchased, or
entrusted to me...

Archaeologist Paryo: I remember how every single collection
item made its way into the research lab.

Archaeologist Paryo: But this one I can't remember! It
seemed to have appeared out of nowhere in the research lab.

Archaeologist Paryo: D-Do you know the true identity of
this!?

Priestess Sophia: I don't have any memories of seeing it
before, but it feels somewhat familiar...

Archaeologist Paryo: Do you have anything special... like
something related to demons?

Mage Relm: Could it be that what Sophia-san is holding is
the ceremonial attire of the demon Namudo?

Archaeologist Paryo: This is just a hypothesis, but this
jewel might be related to the demon Namudo.

Archaeologist Paryo: In my research lab, there are also
relics related to Namudo, the demon. There is a legend that
these artifacts have a mysterious attraction to each
other...

Archaeologist Paryo: It's my request, but I want you to
destroy the jewel.

Thief Nora: Leave it to me! I have confidence in my
strength!

Archaeologist Paryo: There might be something sealed within
this jewel that couldn't be physically destroyed.

Archaeologist Paryo: One thing for certain is that this
jewel is something ominous.
Clea: Understood, leave it to me.
Priestess Sophia: ...Yes, I will carry it and show you.
Clea: Sophia-san, did you say something?

Priestess Sophia: Huh, did I say something... Maybe I've
had too much to drink.
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置
